{
  "name": "ultracode-dynamic-workflow-codex",
  "version": "3.1.0",
  "created_at_utc": "2026-06-14T08:15:26.131766+00:00",
  "skill_name": "ultracode",
  "activation": "$ultracode only",
  "notes": "PACKAGE_MANIFEST.json excludes itself from the file hash list.",
  "primary_changes": [
    "Profile reissued as standalone $CODEX_HOME/<name>.config.toml (top-level keys); legacy [profiles.X] removed (was rejected by Codex >= 0.134). install.py places it at CODEX_HOME root.",
    "Uninstall now prunes ultracode hook groups from hooks.json (preserving unrelated hooks + backup), supports --scope project, and ships a Windows uninstaller.",
    "uc_verify.py shlex-quotes py_compile paths; uc_merge_results.py tolerates missing id column and string findings; uc_adversarial_verify.py guards the delegated subprocess timeout.",
    "Adversarial gate now ingests worker result CONTENT (failing status / high findings block; filename-only results fail strict) and flags shallow syntax-only verification.",
    "Stop hook verifies durable artifacts + adversarial gate status (not wording), with an escape valve so it cannot loop when stop_hook_active is absent.",
    "Hook router emits Codex-native top-level permissionDecision/additionalContext (Claude hookSpecificOutput kept for compatibility); destructive-command detection is quote-aware and broader; PreToolUse no longer gates on a Claude-specific tool name.",
    "Packaging: install ignores __pycache__; uc_check_package.py adds an agents/ vs ultracode/agents/ drift check; spawn prompt inlines per-role developer_instructions as a named-agent fallback and notes max_threads concurrency."
  ],
